meta {
  name: By id credit-term
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

get {
  url: {{host}}/api/{{bu_code}}/credit-term/:id
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  x-app-id: {{x_app_id}}
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

query {
  ~version: 
}

docs {
  ## Get Credit Term by ID
  ดึงรายละเอียดของเงื่อนไขการชำระเงินเฉพาะ รวมถึงรหัส ชื่อ และจำนวนวัน ใช้เมื่อตรวจสอบหรือกำหนดเงื่อนไขการชำระเงินให้ผู้ขาย

  Retrieves the details of a specific payment term including its code, name, and number of days, used when reviewing or assigning vendor payment conditions.

  ### Path Parameters
  | Name | Type | Description |
  |------|------|-------------|
  | `bu_code` | string | Business unit code |
  | `id` | string (UUID) | Credit term ID |

  ### Query Parameters
  | Name | Type | Required | Default | Description |
  |------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
  | `version` | string | No | latest | API version |

  ### Headers
  | Name | Required | Description |
  |------|----------|-------------|
  | `Authorization` | Yes | `Bearer {{access_token}}` |
  | `x-app-id` | Yes | `{{x_app_id}}` |

  ### Permissions
  > Permission key not found in seed; review needed.

  ### Sample Response
  ```json
  {
    "data": {
      "id": "019638a6-2a00-7c4f-8e46-9b7a52c80c4d",
      "code": "NET30",
      "name": "Net 30 Days",
      "days": 30,
      "description": "Payment due within 30 days of invoice date",
      "is_active": true,
      "audit": {
        "created_at": "2026-04-29T08:30:00.000Z",
        "created_by": { "id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890", "name": "John Doe" },
        "updated_at": "2026-04-29T08:30:00.000Z",
        "updated_by": { "id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567891", "name": "Jane Smith" },
        "deleted_at": null,
        "deleted_by": null
      }
    },
    "paginate": null,
    "status": 200,
    "success": true,
    "message": "Success",
    "timestamp": "2026-04-29T08:30:00.000Z"
  }
  ```

  ### Error Responses
  | Status | When |
  |--------|------|
  | 401 | Missing or invalid bearer token |
  | 403 | User lacks permission to view credit terms |
  | 404 | Credit term with the given `id` not found |

  > Service-layer errors propagate via TCP; see micro-business for full list.
}

params:path {
  id: {{credit_term_id}}
}
